    <node id="Cebpa" name="CEBPa" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="Cebpa_gene | Cebpa_ER"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.ensembl.org/Mus_musculus/Gene/Summary?db=core;g=ENSMUSG00000034957;r=7:35119293-35121928"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15589173"/>
          <link xlink:href="ttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15163413"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>CEBPa is expressed in myeloid lineage and necessary for granulcytic development.

CEBPa is necessary for CMP to GMP transition ; necessary for general myelopoiesis ; not for GMP to Neutrophile.
[Zhang P et al. (2004) Immunity 21:853-63]

Ectopic expression in B cells induces their reprogramming into macrophage.
[Xie H et al. Cell. 2004 May 28;117(5):663-76]




</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="251" y="370" style="Mac"/>
    </node>
    <node id="Csf1r" name="M-CSFR" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="Spi1 &amp; !Pax5_prot_active"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.ensembl.org/Mus_musculus/Gene/Summary?db=core;g=ENSMUSG00000024621;r=18:61105572-61132149"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10498603"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Necessary for monocyte differentiation.

Constitutive expression in PU1-- myeloid cell line allowed recovering of survival but not myeloid differentiation.
[Anderson K. L. et al. (1999) Blood, 94(7)]</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="110" y="312" style="Mac"/>
    </node>
