      <nodevisualsetting x="123" y="239" style="Mac (small)"/>
    </node>
    <node id="Spi1" name="Spi1" maxvalue="2">
      <value val="2">
        <exp str="(Runx1 &amp; Spi1 &amp; (Cebpa | Cebpb) &amp; Csf1r_act) | (Runx1 &amp; Spi1 &amp; !(Gfi1 | (Foxo1 &amp; Ikzf1)))"/>
      </value>
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="(Spi1 &amp; Runx1 &amp; !(((Cebpa | Cebpb) &amp; Csf1r_act) | (Foxo1 &amp; !Ikzf1) | !Gfi1)) | (Foxo1 &amp; Ebf1 &amp; Ikzf1 &amp; !(Spi1 | Runx1))"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.ensembl.org/Mus_musculus/Gene/Summary?db=core;g=ENSMUSG00000002111;r=2:91082390-91115756"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www-ncbi-nlm-nih-gov.insb.bib.cnrs.fr/pubmed/16923394"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www-ncbi-nlm-nih-gov.insb.bib.cnrs.fr/pubmed/19818654"/>
          <link xlink:href=""/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Necessary for myeloid and lymphoid differentiation.

2 levels of activity: 
- low level control B cell or granulocyte differentiation, 
- high level control monocyte differentiation.
[﻿Laslo P et al. (2006) Cell 126:755-66] 
[Spooner C et al. (2009)  Immunity, 31(4), 576–86]

</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="367" y="298" style="Progenitors [2]"/>
    </node>
