        <exp str="Foxo1_gene"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.ensembl.org/Mus_musculus/Gene/Summary?db=core;g=ENSMUSG00000044167;r=3:52268336-52353221;t=ENSMUST00000053764"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17254970"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>FoxO1 knock-out mice has less mature B and T cells and HSC with impaired self renewal
[Tothova, Z. (2007) Cell, 128(2)]


</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="856" y="449" style="Bcell"/>
    </node>
    <node id="Ebf1" name="EBF" maxvalue="1">
      <value val="1">
        <exp str="Ebf1_gene"/>
      </value>
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href="http://www.ensembl.org/Mus_musculus/Gene/Summary?db=core;g=ENSMUSG00000057098;r=11:44617317-45008091"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7542362"/>
          <link xlink:href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15767371"/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Necessary for B cell differentiation.

KO block B cell development at a proB B220+ Bp1-- HSA-- stage   
[﻿Lin H, Grosschedl R (1995) Nature 376:263–267]

In IL-7 knock-out, overexpression of Ebf1 rescue B cell potential of CLP 
[﻿S. Dias et al.,The Journal of experimental medicine 201, 971-9 (2005)]</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="815" y="537" style="Bcell"/>
    </node>
