    <node id="Il7" maxvalue="1" input="true">
      <annotation>
        <linklist>
          <link xlink:href=""/>
        </linklist>
        <comment>Required for B cells differentiation.

- KO entails impairs in lymphoid compartiment 
(U. von Freeden-Jeffry et al., Immunity 7, 147-54 (1997).)

- KO impairs selectivly B potential of CLP, not T or NK (﻿1. S. Dias et al.,The Journal of experimental medicine 201, 971-9 (2005).
- - Can be partially rescue by overexpression of EBF
- - Nearly not rescue by overexpression of Pax5

- KO block B development at the prepro stage (﻿1. K. Kikuchi et al., The Journal of experimental medicine 201, 1197-203 (2005).

- KO downregulate EBF and Pax5 (4w+, adult++) (﻿1. S. Dias et al.,The Journal of experimental medicine 201, 971-9 (2005).

</comment>
      </annotation>
      <nodevisualsetting x="965" y="37" style="Bcell"/>
    </node>
